rs', extracted_content='**Walmart Tax‑Exemption Enrollment Attempt – Summary**\n\n- Started from https://www.walmart.com.\n- Located the official Tax Exempt Program page (https://www.walmart.com/cp/tax-exemption-program/8480422).\n- Found the individual application link (https://www.walmart.com/taxexempt/orgform) and followed it.\n- Reached the Walmart Business login page (identity.walmart.com) and entered a business email (testbusiness@example.com).\n- Attempted to click the Continue button multiple times (indexes 5 and 6) but the page did not navigate forward; no password or further fields appeared.\n- All alternative navigation attempts (search, footer links, Services menu, direct URLs) were exhausted without reaching the enrollment form.\n\n**Current Status**: On the Walmart Business login page with email entered; enrollment flow cannot proceed automatically because additional verification steps are required (e.g., password entry, email verification, or account creation steps not exposed to automation).\n\n**Next Manual Steps Required**:\n1. Complete the sign‑in or account‑creation process on the login page (enter password or follow the email verification link that will be sent).\n2. After successful sign‑in, navigate to the Tax Exempt Program enrollment form (should be accessible from the Business account dashboard or via the original application link).\n3. Fill out the required organization details (EIN/Tax ID, organization name, address, etc.) and submit.\n4. Capture the final confirmation page or email confirming enrollment.\n\nThe automated attempt has been documented in `results.md`. Further manual interaction is needed to finish the enrollment.\n\n*Note*: The task required using only the starting website (walmart.com). All possible automated paths have been explored.\n\n**File attached**: results.md\n\nAttachments:\n\nresults.md:\n# Walmart Tax‑Exemption Enrollment Attempt\n\n**Current Status**\n- Navigated to the Walmart Tax Exempt Program page: https://www.walmart.com/cp/tax-exemption-program/8480422\n- Located the individual application link: https://www.walmart.com/taxexempt/orgform\n- Followed the link, which redirected to the Walmart Business login page: https://identity.walmart.com/account/login?tp=B2BMiddleware&client_... (or similar)\n- Entered a business email (testbusiness@example.com) and attempted to click **Continue** multiple times (indexes 5 and 6) but the flow did not advance.\n\n**What Remains**\n- A Walmart Business account must be successfully created or signed into to access the actual tax‑exemption enrollment form.\n- After account creation, the enrollment form will request additional details (EIN/Tax ID, organization name, address, etc.).\n\n**Next Steps for Completion**\n1. Complete the Walmart Business account creation process (provide a valid business email, set a password, verify the email, etc.).\n2. Once logged in, revisit the individual application link (https://www.walmart.com/taxexempt/orgform) to access the enrollment form.\n3. Fill out the required organization information and submit.\n4. Capture the final confirmation page or reference number as proof of enrollment.\n\n**Conclusion**\nThe automation has reached the point where user interaction (account creation) is required. The enrollment cannot be fully completed without a valid business account. The steps above outline what is needed to finish the process.\n\n## Current Progress\n- Navigated to Walmart Tax Exempt Program overview page.\n- Located the individual application link (`https://www.walmart.com/taxexempt/orgform`).\n- Followed the link, which redirected to the Walmart Business login page.\n- Entered a test business email (`testbusiness@example.com`).\n- Attempted to click the Continue button multiple times (indexes 5 and 6) and even sent an Enter key, but the page did not advance to the next step (password entry or account creation).\n- Explored alternative paths (footer links, Services menu, direct URLs) without success.\n\n## Remaining Steps to Complete Enrollment\n1. Use a valid business email associated with a Walmart Business account.\n2. After clicking Continue, complete the password entry (or account creation) flow.\n3. Once logged in, navigate to the tax‑exempt application form (`https://www.walmart.com/taxexempt/orgform`).\n4. Fill out required fields: Business name, EIN/Tax ID, address, etc.\n5. Submit the form and capture the confirmation page or reference number.\n\n## Notes\n- The login flow may require additional verification (e.g., OTP) that cannot be automated without user interaction.\n- If the email is not recognized, the system may prompt to create a new account; ensure the "Create free account" path is followed.\n- After successful login, the enrollment form should be accessible directly from the Tax Exempt Program page.\n\n**Status**: Enrollment not completed. Further manual interaction is required to finish the process.\n', include_extracted_content_only_once=False, metadata=None, include_in_memory=False)], all_model_outputs=[{'go_to_url': {'url': 'https://www.walmart.com', 'new_tab': False}, 'interacted_element': None}, {'write_file': {'file_name': 'todo.md', 'content': '# Walmart Tax-Exemption Enrollment Task\n\n## Goal\nEnroll for tax-exemption on Walmart.com using the starting website.\n\n## Steps\n- [ ] Search for "tax exemption" using the site search bar.\n- [ ] Review search results and locate the official tax exemption enrollment page.\n- [ ] If needed, sign in to an account (Sign In link index 5).\n- [ ] Follow the enrollment process, filling any required forms.\n- [ ] Confirm enrollment completion.\n- [ ] Document the final confirmation details in results.md.\n', 'append': False, 'trailing_newline': True, 'leading_newline': False}, 'interacted_element': None}, {'input_text': {'index': 2, 'text': 'tax exemption', 'clear_existing': True}, 'interacted_element': DOMInteractedElement(node_id=234, backend_node_id=310, frame_id=None, node_type=<NodeType.EL